<table class="current map-data">
  <tr>
    <td>State</td>
    <td>Population</td>
  </tr>
  <% State.all.each do |state| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= state.name %></td>
        <td><%= state.population %></td>
      </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<div id='map_canvas' class="left"></div>
<div class="description left">
  <h2>Excerpt From "Planning Commission Of India"</h2>

  <div>
    Health should be viewed as not merely the absence of disease but as a state of complete physical, mental and
    social well-being
  </div>
  <div class="bullet">
    <b>1.</b>At the start of the Eleventh Plan, the number of doctors per lakh of population was only 45, whereas, the
    desirable number is 85 per lakh population.
  </div>
  <div class="bullet">
    <b>2.</b>Similarly, the number of Nurses and Auxiliary Nurse and Midwifes (ANMs) available was only 75 per lakh
    population whereas the desirable number is 255.
  </div>

  <div>
    <h4>...The overall shortage is exacerbated by a wide geographical variation in availability across the country.
      Rural
      areas are especially poorly served.</h4>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="form">
  <form action="/add_details" method="POST">
    Number of doctors: <input type="text" name="doctor_count"/> <br/>
    Number of nurses : <input type="text" name="nurse_count" /> <br/>
    <input type="hidden" name="state_code"/>
    <input type="hidden" name="district_code"/>
    <input type="submit" value="Add"/>
  </form>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>